{
  "description": "BigQuery-SQL Server hybrid with aggregate FILTER spelled HAVING-inside-parens, QUALIFY keyword for post-window filtering, hash-line comments, ISNULL for null-safe equality, and upper-case fold with bracket identifiers replaced by preserve-case double-quote identifiers.",
  "divergence_level": "moderate",
  "inspired_by": [
    "bigquery",
    "sql_server",
    "db2"
  ],
  "name": "bqserver_qualify_filter",
  "notes": "Hybrid of BigQuery (QUALIFY post-window filtering concept, 0-based arrays, GROUP BY accepting aliases) and SQL Server (ISNULL spelling for null-safe equality, strict boolean truthiness, integer truncation). WITH is renamed to PREPARE to create a unique CTE surface. The NULLS LAST default for DESC ordering (matching neither Postgres nor Oracle convention) and ISNULL null-safe-eq operator are the sharpest divergence points. Comments use hash-line style from DB2/MySQL lineage. Window frame defaults to ROWS UNBOUNDED TO CURRENT rather than RANGE.",
